pageContext.claim: “If any state does not want to share this information, one has to wonder what they're worried about. And I ask the vice president and I ask the commission: What are they worried about?”
pageContext.analysis: There are several lawsuits filed against the voting commission over concerns that the commission's demand for voter information may violate federal and state privacy laws. Yet Trump suggests that states deciding not to share the information are up to something nefarious.
